The paper discusses the use of caching and network coding to improve video streaming in wireless networks, which falls under the categories of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also specifically focuses on video content (cs.MM) and considers the trade-offs between memory usage and video quality (cs.DC). Finally, the paper proposes a new decentralized scheme for cache-aided delivery (cs.SI).
